    "# Credit Card Fraud Detection — Machine Learning\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "This project builds machine learning models to detect fraudulent credit card transactions.\n",
    "\n",
    "Fraud detection is a real-world classification problem with two major challenges:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Fraud cases are very rare\n",
    "- Fraud patterns are often behavioral rather than obvious\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we prepare the data, engineer useful features, train multiple models, and evaluate them using metrics that are appropriate for imbalanced datasets.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "The main goals of this notebook are to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Load and prepare the dataset\n",
    "2. Clean unnecessary columns\n",
    "3. Engineer useful features from dates and time\n",
    "4. Encode categorical variables\n",
    "5. Build baseline and stronger machine learning models\n",
    "6. Handle class imbalance\n",
    "7. Compare model performance\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why accuracy is not enough\n",
    "\n",
    "Because fraud cases make up only a very small portion of the dataset, accuracy can be misleading.\n",
    "\n",
    "For example, a model could predict every transaction as non-fraud and still get very high accuracy.\n",
    "\n",
    "That is why this notebook focuses more on:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Precision**\n",
    "- **Recall**\n",
    "- **F1-score**\n",
    "- **ROC-AUC**"
   ]
  },
